SEC. 4.

Qualifications of Board Members.

芒聙聰 The members of the Board shall at the time of appointment:

Be a citizen of the Philippines;

Be a holder of the degree of Engineer of Mines, E. M.; Bachelor of Science in Mining Engineering, B. S. E. M., conferred by any engineering school or college, legally chartered and of good standing;

Be registered and legally qualified to practice mining engineering in the Philippines;

Has been engaged in the actual practice of mining engineering, metallurgical engineering and/or geology for at least ten years, five of which must be in the field of mining engineering;

Not to be member of the faculty of any school, college or university, where a regular course in mining engineering, geology and/on metallurgy is taught, nor have a pecuniary interest in such institution;

Recommended by the corresponding bona-fide professional mining engineering society.

SEC. 16.

Qualifications of Applicants for Mine and/or Quarry Foreman.

芒聙聰 Any person applying for a certificate of registration as mine and/or quarry foreman shall, prior to his admission for certification, establish to the satisfaction of the Board that:

He is at least twenty-one years of age;

If a foreigner, his country accords reciprocity with the Philippines;

He is of good reputation and moral character;

He has completed a mining and/or quarry course of instruction from a vocational or trade school or correspondence school of known standing or from any mining company training course or its equivalent; or

He has at least five years actual experience in mining and/or quarrying.

SEC. 25.

Personnel Required in Mineral Exploitation and/ or Quarrying.

芒聙聰 Every mining works, project, and/or quarrying operation shall have not less than the following complement of resident mining engineers and/or foremen duly registered under this Act:

Twenty-five persons but not more than fifty persons for the entire operation directly engaged in mining and/or quarrying operation, a registered foreman is required;

Over fifty persons but not more than one hundred persons for the entire operation directly engaged in mining and/or quarrying operation, one registered mining engineer and one registered foreman are required;

Twenty-five persons but not more than seventy-five persons per shift, directly engaged in mining and/or quarrying operation, one registered foreman per shift and one registered mining engineer for the entire operation;

Over seventy-five persons per shift, directly engaged in mining and/or quarrying operation, shall require a registered foreman and a registered mining engineer for each shift:

Provided,

That all persons acting as mine superintendent or its equivalent, and the mine engineer, shall be registered mining engineers.
